":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Late Latin name <i>Mauricius</i>, a derivative of <i>Maurus</i> (a byname meaning ‘Moor’, i.e. ‘dark, swarthy’), borne by, among others, an early Byzantine emperor (  <i>c.</i>539–602 ). It was introduced to Britain by the Normans and was popular in the Middle English period, but was not widely adopted by the nobility and became rare in the 17th century. Between the mid-19th century and the 1940s, it was moderately popular but has since faded again.  See also  Morris ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Maurice Drummond was born in 1075, in Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Malcolm Drummond 2nd Thane of Lennox. She died in Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1075–":"1075–Surnud","1075–1131":"1075–1131","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1075–Female":"1075–Surnud","Abt 1100":"umbes 1100","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1131":"1131","1075":"1075","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1075–":"1075–Kuollut","1075–1131":"1075–1131","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1075–Female":"1075–Kuollut","Abt 1100":"noin 1100","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1131":"1131","1075":"1075","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1075–":"1075–Décédée","1075–1131":"1075–1131","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1075–Female":"1075–Décédée","Abt 1100":"environ 1100","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1131":"1131","1075":"1075","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Maurice Drumm